s="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/27/2" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2007.27.issue-2/asset/14a16856-6614-1685-3661-a1685636614a/radiographics.2007.27.issue-2.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">409</span> - <span property="pageEnd">429</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17374861/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17374861</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.272065034">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FDG+%3D+fluorodeoxyglucose&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FDG = fluorodeoxyglucose</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SCC+%3D+squamous+cell+carcinoma&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SCC = squamous cell carcinoma</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SUV+%3D+standardized+uptake+value&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SUV = standardized uptake value</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The various surgical techniques used in esophageal cancer surgery are reviewed, and the imaging features associated with a variety of postoperative anatomic changes, intra- and postoperative complications, and tumor recurrence are discussed and illustrated.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Tae Jung</span> <span property="familyName">Kim</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (T.J.K., K.H.L., Y.H.K., K.W.L.) and Thoracic Surgery (S.W.S., S.J., S.-K.C.), Seoul National University Bundang Hospital, Seoul National University College of Medicine, 300 Gumi-dong, Bundang-gu, Seongnam-si, Gyeonggi-do 463-707, South Korea; and the Institute of Radiation Medicine, Seoul National University Medical Research Center, Seoul, South Korea (T.J.K., K.H.L., Y.H.K., K.W.L.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 20, 2006; revision requested May 31; final revision received September 20; accepted September 25. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Kim/Tae+Jung" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Kyoung Ho</span> <span property="familyName">Lee</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (T.J.K., K.H.L., Y.H.K., K.W.L.) and Thoracic S